    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix socket resource leak in LDPC generator tools by removing ASAN leak detection disable\n\n### Summary\nThe LDPC code generator tools were incorrectly disabling AddressSanitizer leak detection through the `__asan_default_options()` function. This was hiding potential resource leaks in the tools. The function was inappropriately copied from simulation tools where it's acceptable to disable leak detection.\n\nThis fix removes the `__asan_default_options()` function from the generator tools to allow proper leak detection.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/main.c`: Removed `__asan_default_options()` function\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_bnProc/main128.c`: Removed `__asan_default_options()` function  \n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_cnProc/main.c`: Removed `__asan_default_options()` function\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_cnProc/main128.c`: Removed `__asan_default_options()` function\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Compile the LDPC generator tools with AddressSanitizer enabled\n2. Run the tools with valid parameters\n3. Observe that resource leaks are not detected due to `detect_leaks=0` being returned by `__asan_default_options()`\n\nAfter the fix, AddressSanitizer will properly detect and report any resource leaks in these generator tools, ensuring they maintain clean resource management practices.\n"
}